	(text "The CLK is divided by two which causes only odd edges (1,3,5, etc...) to\nshift into the shift registers. As many others have noted, the original relays\nlatch and are unlatched using the data on the even clock edges. Because the\nCLK is divided, the shift register will always \"miss\" these even edges, ignoring the data.\n\nAll OpenSource solutions use solid-state devices that do not\nlatch and require the output to always be on. By performing the same divide by two\nlogic to the strobe signal and using it to gate the clock signal, the second\npulse to de-energize the coil driver can also be ignored. This \"latches\" the enable\nsignals for any Photomos or discrete SSR.\n\nThis simplifies a pure logic approach greatly."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 62.738 146.304 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "6135118d-9f89-4af3-b817-fbe4de3bcd7e")
	)
